# Files excluded from the published pub.dev package.
#
# A root `.pubignore` takes precedence over the root `.gitignore` (pub stops
# consulting the `.gitignore` in any directory that has a `.pubignore`), so this
# file restates the relevant ignore rules and then adds publish-only exclusions.

# --- Publish-only exclusions ------------------------------------------------

# Upstream Carbon sources, vendored as git submodules (multiple GB of icons,
# website content, and design kits). They are the porting reference only and
# are never needed by consumers of the package.
documentation/

# Icon/pictogram data-generation tooling and its Python helpers. Build-time
# only — the generated Dart lives under lib/.
tool/

# Tests, goldens, and the upstream-fidelity reference images. Not shipped.
test/

# Project docs. The README's relative links are rewritten to the repository by
# pub.dev, so the docs stay reachable without bloating the archive (and this
# also avoids pub's "rename docs/ to doc/" convention warning).
docs/

# Project-internal contributor/AI guidance and the strict in-repo lint config;
# neither is useful to package consumers.
CLAUDE.md
analysis_options.yaml

# The gallery's Dart sources (example/lib, pubspec, README) are enough for the
# pub.dev example tab; the native build scaffolding would only bloat the archive.
example/android/
example/ios/
example/web/

# --- Mirrored from .gitignore (re-stated because .pubignore overrides it) ----

# Editor / IDE / tooling state.
.idea/
.vscode/
.cursor/
.claude/
.zed/
.agent/
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws
.metadata
skills-lock.json

# Build artifacts and caches.
build/
coverage/
failures/
.dart_tool/
.flutter-plugins-dependencies
**/doc/api/

# Miscellaneous.
*.log
*.pyc
*.swp
.DS_Store
